and each term can be rewritten using `|x - y| = |y - x|`.

#### Step 2: Formal proof using the triangle inequality
First, note that for any real numbers, the absolute value of the sum is less than or equal to the sum of absolute values. So:
```
|ℓ m - ℓ n| = |(ℓ m - RiemannSum (f m) a b M) + (RiemannSum (f m) a b M - RiemannSum F a b M) + (RiemannSum F a b M - RiemannSum (f n) a b M) + (RiemannSum (f n) a b M - ℓ n)|
